Our Reviews 






















We’d love for you to share your Mitchell Christopher Salon experience with us and with the rest of the world.
Click on a button to the left to write a review.





I started patronizing Dean in 1992. He is the only one I allow to cut my hair. Always fun. Always friendly. Always perfect. I only wish he was more willing to discuss politics. – Jeff E.
My wife has Cancer and she asked me to grow my hair long because she lost hers during Chemo. She now asked me to get it cut so we went to Mitchell Christopher and what a great choice that was. Dean was my stylist and he couldn’t have been any nicer. I didn’t get a haircut for over 2 years and didn’t have a good idea on how to proceed. Dean made everything so easy, I look great. Everyone in the Salon were so friendly we didn’t want to leave. My wife while waiting for me also got a haircut (not much hair but she looks great) and they didn’t charge her.I can’t wait for my hair to grow out so I can go back. – Ben
I have never experience such quality as I did at Mitchell Christopher Salon. Let me tell you that my hair was 3 different colors & one of those colors were an ugly black! Dean not only got my hair back to it’s original color, but it was all one color & the cut & style were perfect for me. I can’t wait to go back again! 🙂 – Sarah Medina
I have been to many salons, and some are better and friendlier than others. However, when it was time for me to get a new short hairstyle for the new year, I can only trust Mariefel at Mitchell Christopher Salon because she truly knows what to do with my very thick, coarse and pretty damaged, wavy, long hair. It was that time when I was ready for a change. So I got some color/highlights, keratin treatment and haircut all in one day. Everything was excellent!  Now, thanks to Mariefel and this salon, I have a healthier, shinier and super chic hairstyle that I love. Very happy to report that everyone who has seen my new hairstyle loved it too. – Ruth L.
I looooved my new hair color, so shinny even weeks after. My hair do and makeup for the wedding was absolutely amazing, I looked great in all my photos. Thank you Mariefel for my makeover, can’t wait for the next one! – Argentina Leyva
I live in Waukegan and make the 50 mile trip to get my hair done at Mitchell Christopher Salon!  It is definitely worth the trip. I have been going there since the salon opened and I wouldn’t go anywhere else. The color and cut that Mariefel does is so natural that friends can’t believe that my color is not natural.  When I go in and just don’t know what I want to do with my hair – I leave it up to Mariefel and I have never been disappointed. She is awesome!  The atmosphere in the salon is so welcoming and friendly. The staff is great. – Annie
I’ve been going to Mitchell Christopher for years, and I’ve never been disappointed! I’ve used a few of their stylists, but I’ve been going to Chris for the last few years and absolutely love her! She’s the only stylist I’ve ever been able to go to and say, “I need something different” and she ALWAYS does a great job! Chris and Mariefel even did my hair and makeup for my wedding and it was flawless. The assistants are great and all the stylists are so welcoming….I could never ask for a better salon and staff.  – Melissa
Rachel did my galaxy hair and red dip dye on my hair and it turned out gorgeous. I get compliments literally every day on my purple, pink, blue and green hair. I will keep coming back to Rachel for sure – she always knows what’s on trend and how to do it. – Jessica S.
Love, love, loved this salon! Has a great vibe and is very welcoming. Rachel did highlights and a cut and made my hair look fantastic! She is a Redken certified stylist – which made me confident in her abilities. I always appreciate a clean, friendly, skilled salon. I highly recommend Mitchell Christopher Salon.  Great service and value – you will love it here! – Veronica B.















